# Coding Conventions

## TypeScript

- Strict mode enabled (`"strict": true` in tsconfig)
- Never use `any` -- use `unknown` and narrow, or define proper types
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- Use `as const` for literal tuples and enums
- Import types with `import type { ... }` when only used as types

## React (apps/web)

- Functional components only, no class components
- Custom hooks (`use*`) for reusable logic -- colocate in a `hooks/` folder
- Components in PascalCase files: `PianoRoll.tsx`, `NoteEditor.tsx`
- Keep components small; extract sub-components when > 100 lines
- Use Zustand stores in `stores/` -- one store per domain (songs, notes, auth, ws)

## Hono (apps/api)

- Group routes with `app.route('/prefix', subApp)`
- Middleware as separate files in `middleware/` folder
- Access D1 and DO bindings via `c.env` (typed via `Env` interface in `types.ts`)
- Always validate request body with Zod before processing
- Return consistent JSON: `{ data: T }` on success, `{ error: string, code: string }` on failure

## Naming

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Files | kebab-case | `piano-roll.tsx`, `note-service.ts` |
| Components | PascalCase | `PianoRoll`, `NoteCard` |
| Functions/vars | camelCase | `createNote`, `songId` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE | `MAX_TRACKS`, `MAX_TIME` |
| DB columns | snake_case | `song_id`, `created_at` |
| API routes | kebab-case | `/api/songs/:id/notes` |

## Error Handling

- Never swallow errors with empty catch blocks
- API: throw `HTTPException` from Hono with proper status codes
- Frontend: surface errors to user via toast notifications
- Log errors with context (operation name, relevant IDs)

## Constants

```typescript
const MAX_TRACKS = 8;
const MAX_TIME = 300;
const TRACK_RANGE = { min: 1, max: 8 } as const;
const TIME_RANGE = { min: 0, max: 300 } as const;
```
